      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PERFECTDELIGHT (12) copped a check and broke early in last week's heat so did well to recover for fourth. Had kicked off her campaign with a win at this circuit and distance and was fourth from the widest barrier in a Listed race at Menangle in her only other outing so far this campaign. Tricky draw but she has the talent to overcome it. CHEVAL JULIA (3) came from wider to place when second-up two back at this circuit and distance before a solid fourth in last week's heat. Race fit now and has drawn to advantage. ROCKIN MISS REGINA (1) has come from wider barriers for midfield finishes at her last couple. Better served by the inside draw so worth including at odds. MAMMALS JEWEL (9) is another coming off a decent effort for fifth in her heat and had won well prior. Draws for a trail so could get into the finish.",
